_header: All the worship thou has of kind
_description: Three kinds of honor, in a Latin prose text — three 6-line stanzas translating a Latin poem

WorcF126.First Lines:
All þe worschipe þou hast of cundeas someres flour it
                    will a-swynde…
WorcF126.Last Lines:
…schort and lyȝt and foul with alla liere
                    beyre…
WorcF126.Note: Ends of some lines lost through tearing.
